Let $\vec{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\vec{u} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$. We want to find $k$ such that $\| k \vec{v} - \vec{u} \| = 2 \sqrt{13}.$</think> <answer> We have
\begin{align*}
k \vec{v} - \vec{u} &= \begin{pmatrix} 2k - 4 \\ -3k - 7 \end{pmatrix},\\
\left\| k \vec{v} - \vec{u} \right\| &= \sqrt{(2k - 4)^2 + (-3k - 7)^2} = 2 \sqrt{13}. 
\end{align*}
Quadratic Formula yields $k = \boxed{\frac{13}7, -3}.$</answer>

