The given projection vector $\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$ means that $\mathbf{v} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v}$ is orthogonal to $\mathbf{w}$. Therefore, if $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \\ v_3 \end{pmatrix},$ then
\[\mathbf{v} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} v_1 - 4 \\ v_2 + 2 \\ v_3 - 4 \end{pmatrix}\]is orthogonal to $\mathbf{w} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}.$  This means that
\[2(v_1 - 4) - v_2 + 2(v_3 - 4) = 0 \implies 2v_1 - v_2 + 2v_3 = 16.\]In other words, all vectors $\mathbf{v}$ must lie on the plane $2x - y + 2z = 16.$</think>
(answer) Let $(x,y,z)$ be the coordinates of a vector $\mathbf{v}$ and suppose it lies on the desired plane.  We note that
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{v} - \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} &= \begin{pmatrix} x - 4 \\ y + 2 \\ z - 4 \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \times \frac12 \begin{pmatrix}
x - y \\ y - z \\ z - x \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
and thus
\[\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \times \frac12 \begin{pmatrix}
x - y \\ y - z \\ z - x \end{pmatrix}.\]This is of the form $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} x_0 \\ y_0 \\ z_0 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} a \\ b \\ c \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} x - a \\ y - b \\ z - c \end{pmatrix},$ where $\begin{pmatrix} x_0 \\ y_0 \\ z_0 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} a \\ b \\ c \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix},$ i.e., $\mathbf{v}$ is a linear combination of $\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$ and $2\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}.$  Thus it traces out the line $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} + (2t)\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 + 8t \\ -2 - 4t \\ 4 + 8t \end{pmatrix},$ which is the plane $2x - y + 2z = 16,$ in the form required.  $\square$</answer>
